{"TopicId":223440,"ForumId":119,"TopicTitle":"Is there a way to always show AP, PE height numbers, with no interaction required in UI in the orbit view?","CreatedByName":"yijian huang","CreatedById":231601,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T14:26:27Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"yijian huang","CreatedById":231601,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T14:26:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am playing KSP2 v0.2.1.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the orbit view, is there a way to always show AP, PE height numbers, with no interaction required in UI ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause I always want to create orbit manever for a strictly circle orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I want to see the exact numbers of AP, PE height.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know I can hover over the AP, PE labels to see these numbers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know I can right-click on the label to pin these numbers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I don\u0027t want to repeat these interactions again and again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to show them by default, like in KSP1 ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-02T14:34:11Z\u0022 title=\u002202/02/2024 02:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 2\u0022\u003EFebruary 2\u003C/time\u003E by yijian huang\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Biggen","CreatedById":173719,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T16:02:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou have to look under your nav ball for the AP/PE heights.\u00A0 That is the only way to have them show on screen all the time currently without mousing over them and right-clicking to lock them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-02T16:02:25Z\u0022 title=\u002202/02/2024 04:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 2\u0022\u003EFebruary 2\u003C/time\u003E by Biggen\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T16:39:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224363883\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223440\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221706889730\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173719\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Biggen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Biggen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou have to look under your nav ball for the AP/PE heights.\u00A0 That is the only way to have them show on screen all the time currently without mousing over them and right-clicking to lock them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that doesn\u0027t show AP/PE for a planned maneuver, which is what I think \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E wants. Very much agree that it should be a feature, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Biggen","CreatedById":173719,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T16:59:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224363896\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223440\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221706891982\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022whatsEJstandfor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, whatsEJstandfor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that doesn\u0027t show AP/PE for a planned maneuver, which is what I think \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E wants. Very much agree that it should be a feature, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI misunderstood.\u00A0 Yeah I don\u0027t believe so.\u00A0 That is why I have to use the Maneuver node controller mod.\u00A0 I don\u0027t think I could play without it at this point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022227189\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9771394153\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/214244-maneuver-node-controller-080/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T17:16:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been trying to stay stock for as long as possible but boy oh boy, does that mod look like it\u0027d go down real smooth\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Biggen","CreatedById":173719,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T17:32:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 